1,"A wooden sign with our crown logo greets employees every day at our Vermont headquarters and offices, located in the Champlain Valley of Vermont."
2,"Our Tata Harper gardens are full of activity each Spring as we plant seeds, bulbs and seedlings for each year’s annuals."
3,"Here, Dominique plants bulbs for annual flowers in our Tata Harper gardens. Some flowers and herbs we grow include roses, chamomile, peonies, snapdragons, poppies, tulsi, lavender, calendula, and lemon balm."
4,"We dry many of our own flowers and herbs in an on-site greenhouse. After drying, the flowers are gathered to be measured, sorted and prepared for maceration. Maceration is the process of infusing carrier oils (such as organic olive oil or jojoba) with the benefits of the raw botanical by soaking the material in the oil for multiple days. The material is then filtered out of the oil, which is now a new color and scent, fully infused with the"
5,"Helichrysum, also known as “immortelle,” is a dried flower that we bring from the mountains of Albania."
6,"Dried calendula is sorted and selected; some of these particular flowers will go into our Herbal Tea, a blend of skin-friendly herbs used for infusing spa steam water with balancing, healing and restorative benefits."
7,"Bags of freshly dried herbs in our storage room wait to be incorporated into our oil-based skincare formulas, such as our Revitalizing Body Oil and Replenishing Nutrient Complex. On this shelf are Comfrey, Peppermint, Red Clover, Comfrey and Arnica Flower."
8,"Dried calendula is sorted and selected; some of these particular flowers will go into our Herbal Tea, a blend of skin-friendly herbs used for infusing spa steam water with balancing, healing and restorative benefits."
9,"A bag of calendula, picked last November, is stored carefully for future use. Once dried, these flowers can be stored practically infinitely, so these stores of dried botanicals allows us to create fresh macerations throughout the fall and winter, after the growing season has ended."
10,"Helichrysum, also known as “immortelle,” is a dried flower that we bring from the mountains of Albania."
11,"French Pink Clay is used in our Resurfacing Mask, Refreshing Cleanser and Regenerating Cleanser to aid in drawing out impurities from the skin and deeply cleansing, as an effective alternative to soaps or detergents."
12,"Lavender grows well in our Vermont soil, which contains a lot of clay. It thrives on a particularly sunny field slope of our garden. Here, our handpicked lavender fills the lab with its relaxing, calming scent. This plant has been used for thousands of years to help promote deep sleep and relaxation; it’s an active ingredient in our Aromatic Bedtime Treatment, among other products."
